1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,679
If he agrees to work under me for a week,

2
00:00:02,680 --> 00:00:04,839
I’ll let my team help him.

3
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:07,040
Phi accepted Tae’s challenge.

4
00:00:07,065 --> 00:00:08,825
I think we can handle it by ourselves.

5
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:10,896
I’m applying to be your camera operator.

6
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:11,920
Am I still in time?

7
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Here.

8
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:15,920
Yong asked me to give you this.

9
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:17,880
Take good care of it

10
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:20,680
and don’t leave me again this time,

11
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:22,680
Mr. Producer.

12
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:28,920
Okay.

13
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:28,760
Phi.

14
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:34,120
Phi, how did we end up here?

15
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:37,960
Can I have one more glass?

16
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,280
Tam.

17
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,800
Tam.

18
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:11,760
Tam!

19
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,040
What?

20
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,120
What were you daydreaming about?

21
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:20,280
I was trying to think of
a location for your show.

22
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:23,600
Nowhere would let us film
once they find out it’s your show.

23
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:25,160
Ugh.

24
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:28,280
Is there really nowhere we can film?

25
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:32,240
Hey, Nhudee.

26
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:34,456
What did the village
near the factory in Bang Kruai say?

27
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:35,840
I checked twice.

28
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,560
They said they’d rather
smell polluted water than see your face.

29
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,800
We can cross that place off then.

30
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:43,520
Hey, Gie.

31
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,920
What about the fruit farm
affected by saline soil?

32
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:49,479
They said they’d rather deal with
saline soil than you, Phi.

33
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,599
Oh.

34
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,280
Am I really that bad?

35
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,680
Tam,

36
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,680
what should we do?

37
00:02:55,720 --> 00:02:58,200
At this rate, we’re going to miss
the deadline for the episode.

38
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,840
Guys!

39
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:11,200
The owner of the coffee farm
who rejected us has changed their mind.

40
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:13,440
See?

41
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:15,320
There are kind people out there.

42
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,120
But they want to throw coffee on you first.

43
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:23,240
So no one really will forgive me?

44
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,800
Don’t give up hope just yet.

45
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,800
How about I ask them
to throw cold coffee instead?

46
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,360
Make sure they don’t put ice in it.

47
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,800
Got it.

48
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,320
Will we make it?

49
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,400
Actually, there’s one place.

50
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,400
But I don’t know if you’ll agree.

51
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,000
Where?

52
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,920
Right now, I’d go anywhere.

53
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:53,960
Your home.

54
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:09,720
No way.

55
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,800
I’ll never agree.

56
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,800
There’s no topic we can cover at my home.

57
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:16,560
There are people in trouble
all over the country.

58
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,400
Well…

59
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:20,960
No.

60
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,280
I won’t go there.

61
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:23,120
Are you fighting with your mom?

62
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,360
No.

63
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,759
Then there’s no problem.

64
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:27,760
Think about it.

65
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,600
Your family works in salt farming.

66
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,360
Your mom is the community leader.

67
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:33,360
The people who know things

68
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,280
inside out are your family.

69
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:37,280
Even if the whole country hates you,

70
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:39,680
people from your home really love you.

71
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,080
No, it’s…

72
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,800
What?

73
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,480
You don’t understand.

74
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,640
Trust me.

75
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,960
Let’s cover your family’s story.

76
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,000
Phi,

77
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,536
the coffee farm owner called and asked

78
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:58,016
if you’d let them throw coffee at you.

79
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,640
What do you say?

80
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,400
Please wait a second.
I’m asking him now.

81
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:03,880
Would you let them do it?

82
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,680
Fine.

83
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,360
My home it is.

84
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:12,656
Cancel their appointment, Nhudee.

85
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:13,680
Okay.

86
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,080
No throwing coffee.

87
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,280
Seriously?

88
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:19,720
What now?

89
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,840
If you really want to go to my house,

90
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:22,480
Yeah.

91
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:23,520
I have a condition.

92
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,640
You have to do one thing I say.

93
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:31,520
Okay.

94
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,120
Deal.

95
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:38,560
Is this really his show?

96
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:34,320
BANGKOK-SAMUT SONGKHRAM

97
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,680
I miss you, Mom.

98
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:43,720
I’m going to visit you at home.

99
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,720
There’s dust in my eyes.

100
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,320
I’m not crying.

101
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,840
It’s true.

102
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,480
See you soon, Mom.

103
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,520
Okay.

104
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,120
Hey, do you think
my mom knows I’m crying?

105
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:01,560
Am I convincing?

106
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,880
Yeah, you’re good.

107
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:04,680
Perfectly convincing.

108
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,080
She doesn’t know.

109
00:07:07,360 --> 00:07:08,680
Here, blow your nose.

110
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,640
You can keep it.

111
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,640
Thank you so much, bestie.

112
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:22,400
What would I do without you?

113
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:24,560
Those of you with tickets can board now.

114
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:25,880
We’re leaving soon.

115
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:26,920
Let’s go.

116
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:34,760
What?

117
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,480
I lost my ticket.

118
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:40,599
I couldn’t even take care of one ticket.

119
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:44,280
No wonder Paul doesn’t want me.

120
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,159
I kept it for you.

121
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:48,240
I knew you’d lose it
if you kept it yourself.

122
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:49,040
Here.

123
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:51,320
Oh, buddy.

124
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:54,280
You’re the best.

125
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:57,240
You really pay attention to me.

126
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,520
Sorry.

127
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:13,720
Thank you so much for coming with me.

128
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,600
It’s alright.

129
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,480
Your home is still the same.

130
00:08:57,760 --> 00:08:59,056
It reminds me of when I first came here.

131
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,200
Why are you being emotional?

132
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:03,720
There you are!

133
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:05,079
Hi, Mom.

134
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,080
Hi.

135
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:10,800
I told you to call when you arrived so I’d
have a car pick you up from the main road.

136
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:13,000
I’ve been walking home since I was a kid.

137
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:13,920
I’m used to it.

138
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:15,376
- Let me hug you.
- You’re used to it,

139
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:18,200
but Tam would find it hot.

140
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,479
Come on, Mom.

141
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,320
I’m right here!

142
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,440
Finally, we meet.

143
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,640
Phi often told me about you.

144
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:27,640
He told me about you too.

145
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:30,320
So we’re close now.

146
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:32,119
Let’s go inside.

147
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,120
- Okay.
- Come on.

148
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Oh.

149
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,600
Even my mom doesn’t love me.

150
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,800
I haven’t seen you in so long, Tam.

151
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,840
I missed you.

152
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,120
How are you?

153
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,080
I’m good.

154
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,320
How are you?

155
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:48,279
We’re good, Mom.

156
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:50,360
It’s been so long.
We missed you so much.

157
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:53,719
We didn’t come here alone.

158
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:55,199
That’s Gaogie and Nhudee.

159
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,120
- Hello.
- Hello.

160
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:56,880
Hello.

161
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:57,920
Let’s go in.

162
00:09:57,921 --> 00:09:59,200
I’ve cooked for you.

163
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:00,800
I missed you.

164
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:01,240
Stop it.

165
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,320
You didn’t hug me earlier.

166
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:04,440
Oh, I missed you.

167
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:20,520
Be careful.

168
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,000
Thank you.

169
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,800
The tripod is expensive.

170
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,040
Okay, great.

171
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:36,560
Did you bring all the equipment?

172
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:38,120
Of course.

173
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:40,000
I completed the equipment checklist too.

174
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,640
Where’s the wireless mic?

175
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:42,720
Right here.

176
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:43,760
Camera charger?

177
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,800
Over there.

178
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:45,720
Lenses?

179
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,760
Right here.

180
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:50,200
Gie, I’m not a child.

181
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,600
I wouldn’t make any mistakes.

182
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,400
Really?

183
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:56,200
Where’s the camera memory card?

184
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:57,680
It’s here.

185
00:10:58,360 --> 00:10:59,360
Wait.

186
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,800
Where is it?

187
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:02,680
Hey.

188
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:05,840
It’s here.

189
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,680
I saw you left it on your desk.

190
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,760
I knew you’d forget it.

191
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,880
I’m sorry.

192
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:15,680
I won’t forget it next time.

193
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,000
It’s okay.

194
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:19,760
Come on.

195
00:11:19,761 --> 00:11:21,360
Let’s carry our stuff inside.

196
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,320
This place is still the same.

197
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:37,000
Right?

198
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:40,160
Everything is still
just like when you were here.

199
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,160
So,

200
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:44,640
how many years now?

201
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,240
27.

202
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:47,600
Not your age.

203
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:50,680
I’m asking how long
you’ve been with my son.

204
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,080
Oh.

205
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,440
8 years, Mom.

206
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:56,520
What a relief. I thought
you wouldn’t survive the 7-year curse.

207
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:57,560
Come on, Mom.

208
00:11:57,561 --> 00:11:59,240
There’s no curse.

209
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:01,120
I don’t believe in such a thing.

210
00:12:01,160 --> 00:12:03,120
It depends on the two of us.

211
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:08,319
Let me get you some fruit.

212
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,400
Okay.

213
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,760
You haven’t told her we broke up?

214
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:19,840
Well, I just said
you went to study abroad.

215
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,440
What?

216
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:23,120
Come on.

217
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,639
Just make it convincing.

218
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,520
No, Phi.

219
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:26,480
You’re asking too much.

220
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,800
How am I asking too much?

221
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:30,239
I let you come here to film.

222
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,680
Now keep your promise.

223
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,360
You have to do what I want.

224
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,560
We’re adults.

225
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,840
Yes, we are.

226
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,400
I don’t want to hurt my mom.

227
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,680
You know how much she loves you.

228
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,559
No, I don’t want to lie.

229
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:50,800
Trust me, if you tell her,

230
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,800
she’ll be okay with it.

231
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,400
No, just do as I say.

232
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:53,880
No.

233
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:54,640
Do as I say.

234
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:55,040
No.

235
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:55,640
Do as I say.

236
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:56,080
No.

237
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:56,600
Do as I say.

238
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:57,040
I said no.

239
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:57,920
Do as I say.

240
00:12:57,920 --> 00:12:58,200
No.

241
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:58,720
Do as I say.

242
00:12:58,760 --> 00:12:59,080
No.

243
00:12:59,120 --> 00:12:59,320
Do as I say.

244
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:01,320
Here’s some fruit, kids.

245
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,600
Doesn’t it look good?

246
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,440
What were you saying? I heard “No.”

247
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,480
Oh.

248
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:09,040
No…

249
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,200
No sleeping in separate rooms, Mom.

250
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,040
Right?

251
00:13:18,160 --> 00:13:19,200
Right?

252
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:21,560
Of course, no sleeping in separate rooms.

253
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,040
Why would we do that?

254
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,839
Aren’t you shy in front of Mom?

255
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:25,640
How could you say these things?

256
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:26,680
Why would I be shy?

257
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:29,200
We’ve been together for 8 years.

258
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,000
Right, Mom?

259
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:31,040
Yes.

260
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:35,320
What?

261
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:38,560
Hey, the fruit looks so good.

262
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:39,680
Let me have some.

263
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:40,720
Have some fruit.

264
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:44,440
Is that sweet?

265
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,480
So sweet.

266
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:49,280
Great.

267
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,799
Here you go.

268
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,200
Wow, that looks so good, Mom.

269
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,440
Here’s fried pork.

270
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:10,120
Aren’t those three coming to eat?

271
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,320
Oh, they’re setting up the camera.

272
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:14,000
We’ll interview you in the afternoon.

273
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:16,760
What do I have to say?

274
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,640
Actually, there are a lot of questions.

275
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:21,279
Let’s ask Tam.

276
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,120
Hey!

277
00:14:22,121 --> 00:14:23,281
Come brief Mom on the script.

278
00:14:31,800 --> 00:14:32,680
Babe!

279
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,560
Yes?

280
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:34,639
Please brief Mom on the script.

281
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:36,639
She wants to know the questions.

282
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:37,800
You got it, babe.

283
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:40,160
You’re so cute.

284
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,360
Ouch!

285
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,080
Babe,

286
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,680
please talk slowly

287
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,760
so Mom can understand.

288
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:53,680
Okay.

