571
00:30:08,960 --> 00:30:10,800
I’m just thinking about my mom.

572
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:19,480
I’m just thinking about what I’d do
if she’s really gone one day.

573
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:23,320
I haven’t repaid her anything.

574
00:30:26,920 --> 00:30:28,080
Then do it.

575
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:30,400
You still have time.

576
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:34,760
It’s not that easy.

577
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:40,640
I’ve seen her working in the sun and wind
at the salt farm since I was a kid

578
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:45,560
and she was able to afford
sending me to a good university.

579
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:50,240
But now that I have a good life and career

580
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:55,040
she won’t agree
to move to Bangkok with me.

581
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:00,640
You have to understand her.

582
00:31:01,240 --> 00:31:03,120
She’s been living like this all her life.

583
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:08,400
You can’t expect her to
change easily just because you mean well.

584
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:13,640
Maybe you need to
let her choose her own path.

585
00:31:15,080 --> 00:31:16,640
I know.

586
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:19,680
I just want her to be more comfortable.

587
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,360
Being more comfortable

588
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:31,200
might not be what your mom wants.

589
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:36,760
She might be happy working in
salt farming. I think she’s cool.

590
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:39,320
True.

591
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:41,720
My mom is so cool.

592
00:31:43,080 --> 00:31:46,160
I grew up on a salt farm

593
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:50,120
but honestly, when I tried her salt today,

594
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:53,200
I couldn’t even tell the difference.

595
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:03,280
Because you’re such a loser.

596
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:09,040
Please.

597
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:10,560
You’re not even that good.

598
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:11,440
I’m better than you.

599
00:32:11,441 --> 00:32:14,800
Try the salt tomorrow and tell them apart.

600
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:17,760
I can do that. Why else
would your mom love me so much?

601
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:19,440
No, that has nothing to do with it.

602
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:22,560
Where is it?

603
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:25,160
You’re in big trouble, Nhudee.

604
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:32,200
What should I do?

605
00:32:32,240 --> 00:32:35,200
If I can’t find it, we’ll definitely have to reshoot.

606
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:37,240
No!

607
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,360
Who’s there?

608
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:46,800
I’m asking, who’s there?

609
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:59,400
Calm down. It’s me.

610
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:03,920
What are you doing here?

611
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:08,200
Well…I…

612
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:12,160
What’s wrong?

613
00:33:28,720 --> 00:33:29,720
Hey, Gie.

614
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:33,680
I’m sorry.

615
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:36,280
This is all my fault.

616
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:42,280
I knew you’d lose it.

617
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:51,360
Then why are you helping me?

618
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:55,600
When I first started working,

619
00:33:56,120 --> 00:33:57,600
I was just like you.

620
00:33:59,680 --> 00:34:02,080
I once lost a memory card for a show.

621
00:34:03,960 --> 00:34:05,280
Back then,

622
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:09,280
Yong helped me.

623
00:34:11,600 --> 00:34:17,760
He didn’t just help me find the memory card but with many other things too.

624
00:34:19,040 --> 00:34:20,559
Without him,

625
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:22,680
I wouldn’t have it together today.

626
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:28,200
I just want to return the favor.

627
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:34,520
Helping his sister is one way
I can repay him, right?

628
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,640
Come on. Let’s keep looking.

629
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:52,920
Ah!

630
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:55,240
Gaogie, wait for me!

631
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:05,200
You know, I really love
the smell of the blankets at your home.

632
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:09,239
This one still smells just like
it did the first day I came here.

633
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,240
Of course.

634
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:12,000
It hasn’t been washed since.

635
00:35:14,160 --> 00:35:15,160
Really?

636
00:35:15,760 --> 00:35:16,800
Just kidding.

637
00:35:17,120 --> 00:35:18,000
You’re exaggerating.

638
00:35:18,001 --> 00:35:19,280
How can it smell so good?

639
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:22,160
The smell really gives me nostalgia.

640
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:23,800
Huh?

641
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:26,640
It makes me feel nostalgic.

642
00:35:26,680 --> 00:35:28,296
If you’re feeling fatigued, just go to sleep.

643
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:29,360
I said nostalgic.

644
00:35:30,200 --> 00:35:34,600
It means longing for the past.

645
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:36,816
Oh, is that a word
people who studied abroad use?

646
00:35:36,840 --> 00:35:37,160
Yeah.

647
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:37,920
International.

648
00:35:37,960 --> 00:35:39,040
That’s right.

649
00:35:39,600 --> 00:35:40,240
Oh.

650
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:42,600
You’re so slow to catch on.

651
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:46,400
How can it smell so good? Honestly.

652
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:47,880
Smell it if you don’t believe me.

653
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:53,040
Mmm, it smells good.

654
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:11,080
Do you want to share the blanket?

655
00:36:23,360 --> 00:36:24,360
No!

656
00:36:24,640 --> 00:36:25,600
Stop it.

657
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:26,879
Time’s up.

658
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:28,320
Let’s sleep.

659
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:29,160
Fine.

660
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:29,920
Good night.

661
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:31,279
Great, we can share this blanket.

662
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:32,720
You can hug yours like a bolster.

663
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:34,120
You jerk! Give it back!

664
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:39,360
I’m going to sleep now.

665
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:37,360
I’m burning them all!

666
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:39,280
- Get in there!
- Hey, what are you doing?

667
00:37:39,320 --> 00:37:40,160
Hey, hey!

668
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:41,200
What are you doing?

669
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:44,120
The way to forget

670
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:46,800
is to erase everything!

671
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:48,480
You’re so dramatic.

672
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:51,120
I’m burning everything about him!

673
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:52,760
But I’m scared.

674
00:37:52,800 --> 00:37:53,480
Oh?

675
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:54,880
Can you burn them for me?

676
00:37:58,320 --> 00:37:59,880
Fine, what are these?

677
00:38:05,560 --> 00:38:08,200
The name tag
he wrote for all the juniors.

678
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:11,960
Just dump it.

679
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:13,000
Dump it.

680
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:16,120
The photo you took with him.

681
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:16,960
Dump it.

682
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:18,000
Dump it.

683
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:20,800
The doll you won from the claw machine
and wanted to give him.

684
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:21,440
Dump it.

685
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:22,480
Dump it.

686
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:26,760
Your audition file to be a DJ
at the same show as him.

687
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:28,760
Just dump it!

688
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:29,800
Dump it.

689
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:31,840
Just dump everything.

690
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:33,200
This is the last one.

691
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:36,800
Your signature book
that he was the first to sign.

692
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:41,440
Dump it.

693
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:49,400
No, don’t dump it!

694
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:49,880
What?

695
00:38:49,881 --> 00:38:51,200
Don’t dump that!

696
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:52,960
It’s already burning.

697
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:54,240
No!

698
00:38:56,320 --> 00:38:57,640
Don’t burn!

699
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:01,800
Enough.

700
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:08,240
That was close.

701
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:09,200
Ouch!

702
00:39:09,240 --> 00:39:10,640
It’s hot!

703
00:39:12,840 --> 00:39:15,800
I go from being heartbroken
to almost burning my heart.

704
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:21,520
NICE TO MEET YOU. I’M B.
WELCOME TO OUR FACULTY, PHI.

705
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:22,959
NICE TO MEET U.
LOVE YOU.

706
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:24,919
Why are you so hung up on it?

707
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:27,880
It’s just a signature book that he signed.
TAMTAWAN IS PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

708
00:39:28,880 --> 00:39:30,200
I’m not.

709
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:35,960
You said you’d move on.

710
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:38,560
How can you do that if you’re like this?

711
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:42,800
One day, I’ll be able to let go of him.

712
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:46,200
I just wanted to keep this book

713
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:49,280
because it has your signature in it.

714
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:55,520
My signature?

715
00:39:58,080 --> 00:39:59,520
How is my signature important?

716
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:03,000
You’re important to me.

717
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:06,080
You help me with everything

718
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:09,080
without me even asking.

719
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,920
Thank you so much

720
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:18,560
for helping me with everything.

721
00:40:33,160 --> 00:40:34,800
Let’s drink!

722
00:40:34,840 --> 00:40:35,520
Come on!

723
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:37,040
Let’s drink to numb my heart!

724
00:40:37,320 --> 00:40:38,760
Screw it all!

725
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:39,760
Yeah.

726
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:42,600
This is sadness

727
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:47,080
This is what sadness feels like

728
00:40:47,120 --> 00:40:49,800
Get that right

729
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:51,800
Cheers!

730
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:54,080
I cry from pain, nothing to hide

731
00:40:54,120 --> 00:41:01,279
Struggling hard, losing my mind

732
00:41:01,280 --> 00:41:06,280
Looking back on all this time

733
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:14,120
I regret my tears sometimes

734
00:41:14,160 --> 00:41:18,720
But this pain makes me realize

735
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:23,560
My tears this time

736
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:27,520
They’re worthwhile

737
00:42:16,280 --> 00:42:17,280
Phi.

738
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:21,720
Phi, how did we end up here?

739
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:25,440
Can I have one more glass?

740
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,320
Phi.

741
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:07,960
Tawan

742
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:11,880
Mmm.

743
00:45:12,360 --> 00:45:14,360
Tomorrow, I’ll tell my mom the truth

744
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:18,480
that we broke up.

745
00:46:01,760 --> 00:46:03,679
Oh, you’re awake.

746
00:46:03,680 --> 00:46:04,680
Mmm.

747
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:07,000
I’m sorry.

748
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:10,160
I don’t know when I passed out last night.

749
00:46:10,680 --> 00:46:11,680
Mmm.

750
00:46:13,480 --> 00:46:17,080
It’s morning now and we can’t find it.

751
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:18,639
But it’s okay if we lose it.

752
00:46:18,640 --> 00:46:19,640
We can reshoot.

753
00:46:19,800 --> 00:46:21,800
What? Reshoot?

754
00:46:22,680 --> 00:46:24,440
Padtaphi will stress out.

755
00:46:24,480 --> 00:46:25,559
Tam will scold me.

756
00:46:25,560 --> 00:46:26,799
Everyone will blame me

757
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:28,320
and I’ll be stressed, pressured,

758
00:46:28,360 --> 00:46:29,080
and a problem for society.

759
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:30,000
Then I’ll go to jail.

760
00:46:30,001 --> 00:46:31,040
Then what will I do next?

761
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:31,920
I’ll lose my job!

762
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:33,360
Oh, I’ll lose my job!

763
00:46:33,400 --> 00:46:34,400
Stop.

764
00:46:34,600 --> 00:46:36,000
Calm down, Nhudee.

765
00:46:42,120 --> 00:46:43,480
Stop feeling down.

766
00:46:44,280 --> 00:46:46,560
I’ll tell them I lost it.

767
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:48,800
No one would dare scold you.

768
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:54,480
Let’s go back to the house,

769
00:46:54,560 --> 00:46:56,520
take a shower, and get ready to reshoot.

770
00:46:58,280 --> 00:46:59,280
Reshoot…

771
00:47:07,720 --> 00:47:08,720
Nhudee.

772
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:10,120
Hmm?

773
00:47:20,040 --> 00:47:21,040
What?

774
00:47:24,120 --> 00:47:25,120
Hey!

775
00:47:25,800 --> 00:47:26,920
Found it!

776
00:47:27,440 --> 00:47:28,600
You’re right!

777
00:47:28,640 --> 00:47:30,960
Yay, Gaogie!

778
00:47:31,280 --> 00:47:33,280
We found the memory card!

779
00:47:34,640 --> 00:47:35,680
The memory card!

780
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:42,960
Yay!

781
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,000
We found it.

782
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:47,920
Check carefully next time.

783
00:47:49,960 --> 00:47:50,960
Mmm.

784
00:47:58,680 --> 00:47:59,960
Don’t forget to tell your mom.

785
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:00,840
I know.

786
00:48:00,880 --> 00:48:01,880
Good.

787
00:48:02,080 --> 00:48:03,560
I just wanted to remind you.

788
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:05,839
Where did the girls go for a walk
so early this morning?

789
00:48:05,840 --> 00:48:07,599
I didn’t see them when I woke up.

790
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:08,840
Here.

791
00:48:08,920 --> 00:48:11,520
Phi’s favorite braised mackerel.

792
00:48:18,880 --> 00:48:21,479
Come on, let’s eat.

793
00:48:21,480 --> 00:48:22,600
Thank you, Mom.

794
00:48:25,040 --> 00:48:26,040
Thank you.

795
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:30,440
How was last night?

796
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:35,520
You two drank until late.

797
00:48:35,560 --> 00:48:37,400
I didn’t think you’d wake up.

798
00:48:37,960 --> 00:48:40,360
Oh, we’re fine, Mom.

799
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:41,840
It’s nothing.

800
00:48:42,240 --> 00:48:43,280
Very good.

801
00:48:43,520 --> 00:48:45,079
It’s your friend’s first time at our house.

802
00:48:45,080 --> 00:48:46,840
I was worried he wouldn’t be able to sleep.

803
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:49,040
I could sleep.

804
00:48:49,080 --> 00:48:50,480
I slept very well.

805
00:48:50,960 --> 00:48:53,880
I love your blanket.

806
00:48:54,280 --> 00:48:56,480
It’s so soft and smells so nice.

807
00:48:57,560 --> 00:48:59,840
I wash and dry it in the sun.

808
00:48:59,880 --> 00:49:02,000
If you like it, you should come here often.

809
00:49:02,040 --> 00:49:03,440
Come on, let’s eat.

810
00:49:03,480 --> 00:49:07,199
Here’s Phi’s favorite braised mackerel.

811
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:08,280
Wow.

812
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:11,040
I eat this every day.

813
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:14,320
I believe you really love it.

814
00:49:14,360 --> 00:49:15,480
Believe it or not, Tam.

815
00:49:15,720 --> 00:49:17,080
Phi eats it all the time.

816
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:18,359
He eats it when he fails his exams,

817
00:49:18,360 --> 00:49:19,520
when he’s sick,

818
00:49:19,560 --> 00:49:21,520
when he’s sad, when he’s happy,

819
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:22,800
and even when he’s heartbroken.

820
00:49:24,080 --> 00:49:25,080
Sorry.

821
00:49:27,920 --> 00:49:29,360
Come on, Mom.

822
00:49:29,440 --> 00:49:31,400
That teasing hurts.

823
00:49:31,440 --> 00:49:33,560
I was really heartbroken

824
00:49:35,840 --> 00:49:37,400
but I feel better now.

825
00:49:37,880 --> 00:49:39,880
Tam helped me a lot.

826
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:44,240
Mom,

827
00:49:44,960 --> 00:49:46,960
Tam is a really good guy.

828
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:50,440
So good that I wanted
to bring him to meet you

829
00:49:51,160 --> 00:49:53,960
and show you that you don’t have to
worry about me when I’m in Bangkok.

830
00:50:03,400 --> 00:50:07,360
I feel really lucky to have Tam.

831
00:50:10,120 --> 00:50:14,800
So much that I think…

832
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:19,160
I want to be with him

833
00:50:22,040 --> 00:50:23,160
as boyfriends.

834
00:50:25,920 --> 00:50:27,440
Would you be okay with that, Mom?

835
00:50:35,960 --> 00:50:37,480
Let’s eat!

836
00:50:37,520 --> 00:50:38,960
My braised mackerel!

837
00:50:58,560 --> 00:51:00,160
Your food looks as amazing as ever.

838
00:51:00,600 --> 00:51:04,080
By the way, Mom…

839
00:51:09,080 --> 00:51:10,400
I want to tell you something.

840
00:51:16,960 --> 00:51:18,400
Well…

841
00:51:23,920 --> 00:51:26,800
I want to ask you
about the braised mackerel.

842
00:51:26,840 --> 00:51:28,600
Yes, because, uh,

843
00:51:29,200 --> 00:51:30,599
yours is really delicious.

844
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:33,720
It still tastes as good as when I was a kid.

845
00:51:33,760 --> 00:51:35,800
So I want to know

846
00:51:35,840 --> 00:51:38,360
if you can share the recipe
in case I want to make it.

847
00:51:39,720 --> 00:51:44,239
Uh, you need to use the salt from my farm.

848
00:51:44,240 --> 00:51:46,800
Your late father taught me the recipe, Phi.

849
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:49,760
Now this makes me miss him.

850
00:51:51,480 --> 00:51:54,000
I don’t want to leave this place, I guess

851
00:51:54,040 --> 00:51:57,440
because I still want to feel close to him.

852
00:52:01,800 --> 00:52:05,880
You have Tam to take care of you
in Bangkok and I don’t have to worry.

853
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:14,000
You might want to worry.

854
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:19,320
Mom, the thing is,

855
00:52:19,800 --> 00:52:22,800
we actually…

856
00:52:24,720 --> 00:52:27,040
If you’re going to tell me
you broke up, you don’t have to.

857
00:52:33,040 --> 00:52:34,120
I already knew.

858
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:37,920
Oh?

859
00:52:38,720 --> 00:52:39,880
How did you know?

860
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:41,280
I’m your mom.

861
00:52:41,320 --> 00:52:42,760
Of course, I knew.

862
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:48,800
I’m sorry, Mom.

863
00:52:49,160 --> 00:52:51,560
I didn’t want you to worry, so I lied.

864
00:52:51,840 --> 00:52:53,200
I have to apologize too.

865
00:52:53,240 --> 00:52:54,520
It’s alright.

866
00:52:54,560 --> 00:52:57,679
It’s not my business if you love
or break up with each other.

867
00:52:57,680 --> 00:52:58,640
You’re adults now.

868
00:52:58,680 --> 00:52:59,960
You can make your own decisions.

869
00:53:00,320 --> 00:53:05,400
But does pretending to be together
mean you want to get back with him, son?

870
00:53:07,720 --> 00:53:10,800
What are you talking about, Mom?

871
00:53:11,040 --> 00:53:12,920
No way. I’ve moved on.

872
00:53:12,960 --> 00:53:14,000
Really?

873
00:53:15,560 --> 00:53:16,480
Yes.

874
00:53:16,520 --> 00:53:17,520
Hmm?

875
00:53:17,960 --> 00:53:19,960
Since you knew,

876
00:53:20,120 --> 00:53:23,320
I guess we can stop pretending.

877
00:53:23,360 --> 00:53:24,360
Huh?

878
00:53:25,560 --> 00:53:26,840
I’m moving here

879
00:53:27,873 --> 00:53:31,273
so you know we’re just colleagues, Mom.

880
00:53:31,400 --> 00:53:32,280
Give me the omelet.

881
00:53:32,320 --> 00:53:33,320
I want to eat it.

882
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:35,399
Colleagues? If you say so.

883
00:53:35,400 --> 00:53:37,400
Come on, let’s eat.

884
00:53:39,400 --> 00:53:41,000
Why are you doing this?

885
00:53:50,360 --> 00:53:51,880
You didn’t forget anything, right?

886
00:53:52,880 --> 00:53:53,920
No.

887
00:53:54,280 --> 00:53:55,960
Thank you so much.

888
00:53:56,000 --> 00:53:58,560
I’ll pick the angles
where you look your best.

889
00:53:58,920 --> 00:54:01,000
Come back to visit again, girls.

890
00:54:01,040 --> 00:54:02,000
I’m definitely coming back

891
00:54:02,040 --> 00:54:04,160
because your food is amazing.

892
00:54:05,080 --> 00:54:09,599
Wait, I forgot I made
a big pot of braised mackerel.

893
00:54:09,600 --> 00:54:11,000
Let me reheat it.

894
00:54:11,040 --> 00:54:12,800
It’s okay. I got it.

895
00:54:12,840 --> 00:54:14,559
Use the charcoal stove
to make it smell nice.

896
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:15,560
Okay.

897
00:54:16,200 --> 00:54:17,720
Your braised mackerel is so good.

898
00:54:17,760 --> 00:54:18,816
Can you share the recipe with me?

899
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:19,840
You mean it?

900
00:54:20,320 --> 00:54:21,840
You have to use the salt from my farm.

901
00:54:33,440 --> 00:54:34,559
Go wait outside.

902
00:54:34,560 --> 00:54:35,560
Hmm…

903
00:54:36,440 --> 00:54:38,520
What if I say I want to stay here?

904
00:54:41,920 --> 00:54:43,960
Just in case you need my help.

905
00:54:44,280 --> 00:54:46,160
So, can I help you with anything?

906
00:54:47,840 --> 00:54:48,840
Good.

907
00:54:56,400 --> 00:54:59,600
Don’t tell me you’re thinking about
what my mom said at the dining table.

908
00:55:00,080 --> 00:55:01,080
What?

909
00:55:02,120 --> 00:55:04,120
I haven’t said anything.

910
00:55:04,560 --> 00:55:05,560
There.

911
00:55:06,560 --> 00:55:08,440
This means you’re thinking
about the same thing.

912
00:55:08,840 --> 00:55:11,120
See? You really are thinking about it.

913
00:55:11,480 --> 00:55:13,400
Don’t listen to my mom.

914
00:55:13,560 --> 00:55:15,200
It’s nonsense.

915
00:55:16,080 --> 00:55:18,320
But now that I think about
what your mom said,

916
00:55:20,960 --> 00:55:22,800
sometimes I feel like

917
00:55:24,600 --> 00:55:26,240
your acting is real.

918
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:28,960
Don’t you think so, Phi?

919
00:55:30,440 --> 00:55:31,440
Hey!

920
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:35,560
The coals are ages old.

921
00:55:36,200 --> 00:55:37,560
How could they start a fire?

922
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:47,959
Read my lips.

923
00:55:47,960 --> 00:55:52,640
I don’t feel anything for you anymore.

924
00:55:54,440 --> 00:55:55,440
Great.

925
00:55:56,680 --> 00:55:58,680
If you really don’t have feelings for me,

926
00:55:59,920 --> 00:56:01,920
next week when we edit this work,

927
00:56:03,960 --> 00:56:05,840
you can sleep over at my place.

928
00:56:10,000 --> 00:56:11,000
Why not?

929
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:13,280
Deal.

930
00:56:18,080 --> 00:56:24,080
DIRECTED BY PHADUNG SAMAJARN

931
00:56:24,240 --> 00:56:25,560
Remember our promise?

932
00:56:25,600 --> 00:56:27,720
Keep it strictly work.

933
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:28,816
What are you guys doing here?

934
00:56:28,840 --> 00:56:29,920
Smile.

935
00:56:29,960 --> 00:56:31,200
You look disappointed.

936
00:56:31,240 --> 00:56:32,376
Ever since we walked into the house,

937
00:56:32,400 --> 00:56:34,080
your focus has only been on me.

938
00:56:35,200 --> 00:56:38,319
You think I don’t know what you’re thinking?

939
00:56:38,320 --> 00:56:40,040
So much for scolding me.

940
00:56:40,360 --> 00:56:41,840
You’re no different.

941
00:56:42,240 --> 00:56:43,680
I’m so sleepy.

942
00:56:43,720 --> 00:56:46,320
Can you bring Sosay back to the room?
